HEADWORD: Inshore
<hw>In"shore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being near or moving
towards the shore; <as>as, <ex>inshore</ex> fisheries; <ex>inshore</ex>
currents.</as></def> -- <def2><pos>adv.</pos> <def>Towards the shore;
<as>as, the boat was headed <ex>inshore</ex></as>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

